commentPostTextItems.html: So that's our coverage finished in Ireland for the time being. The West Indies win by the slender margin of one point, although Ireland will be pleased with their performance in beating their associate neighbours.

Today Scotland lost their way when seemingly well set, collapsing miserably after Watson departed. For Ireland the undoubted star was Andre Botha who bowled with great control to peg Scotland back, with Ireland impressive in the field

full ball clipped in the air over mid-wicket, nearly another run-out but thy were just home
off the mark with a mis-timed drive to mid-on

commentPostTextItems.html: Fantastic spell there from Botha, great control as he pegged Scotland back

dismissalComment.html: and that's the  game for Ireland, it was on off stump and Drummond played away from his body and got a fine edge through to O'Brien. Umpire Hair raised the finger with no hesitation

milestones.description: Johnston and Niall O'Brien's 57-run partnership is IRE's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 56 between Andrew White and Jeremy Bray
Neil McCallum and Ryan Watson's 94-run partnership is SCOT's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 54 between Hamilton and Ian Stanger
Niall O'Brien has scored 5 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Eoin Morgan's record
Ryan Watson has become the top scorer for SCOT in ODIs with 673 runs, going past Hamilton's 605
Andre Botha has become the top wicket-taker for IRE in ODIs with 23 wickets, going past Kyle McCallan's 21

stories.subTitle: Ireland v Scotland, Quad Series, Stormont
stories.summary: In their final match of the series, against Scotland, Botha picked up 3 for 27 in nine overs after having added 46 with Niall O'Brien as Ireland beat Scotland by 23 runs. But Ireland failed to gain the bonus point point needed to share the series title wi

stories.subTitle: Ireland v Scotland, Quad Series, Stormont
stories.summary: A tight bowling performance from Andre Botha helped Ireland to beat Scotland, but they could not gain the bonus point needed to share the series title with West Indies
